<h1>Broadband Spending</h1>

<p>All data below reflects information as entered by applicants, without validation or error correction.</p>

<div class="page-header">
<h3>Broadband Prices</h3>
</div>

<table class="table table-hover table-condensed">
  <thead><tr>
    <th>Connection Type</th>
    <th>Lines</th>
    <th>Median Price</th>
    <th>25th Percentile</th>
    <th>75th Percentile</th>
  </tr></thead>
<% @item24_dashboard.conn_types.each do |ctype| %>
  <tr>
  	<td><%= ctype %></td>
    <td><%= number_with_delimiter(@item24_dashboard.single_ctype_stats[ctype]['lines']) %></td>
    <td>$ <%= number_with_delimiter(@item24_dashboard.single_ctype_stats[ctype]['price_median'].round(0).to_i) %></td>
    <td>$ <%= number_with_delimiter(@item24_dashboard.single_ctype_stats[ctype]['price_p25'].round(0).to_i) %></td>
    <td>$ <%= number_with_delimiter(@item24_dashboard.single_ctype_stats[ctype]['price_p75'].round(0).to_i) %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %> 
</table> 

<p><small><em>Data based only on FRNs containing a single connection type & speed.  For FRNs that contain multiple connection types or speeds, the data we collect do not currently allow us to allocate costs to the different connections. In addition, our current data do not allow us to seperately identify those funding requests that bundle phone service with broadband; to the extent applicants do so, the prices above are overestimates of broadband pricing.</em></small></p>

<div class="page-header">
<h3>Connectivity-Related Funding Requests: <strong><%= (@item24_dashboard.percent_of_p1 * 100).round(0) %>%</strong> of Priority 1
($<%= (@item24_dashboard.item24_requests.to_f / 1000000).round(0) %> million)</h3>
</div>
<p>Total requests associated with item 24s, excluding cellular-only requests.  Includes phone service to the extent it is bundled on the same funding request with data connections.</p>
<br>

<table class="table table-hover table-condensed">
  <thead><tr>
    <th>Funding Request Connection Type</th>
    <th style="border-top: 0px">Lines</th>
    <th>Requests</th>
  </tr></thead>
<% @item24_dashboard.requests_by_type.each do |conn_type| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= conn_type["type_of_connections"] %></td>
    <td><%= number_with_delimiter(conn_type["lines"].to_i) %></td>
    <td>$ <%= number_with_delimiter(((conn_type["request"]).to_f / 1000).round(0)) %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>
  <tr>
    <td><i>Multiple Connection Types</i></td>
    <td><%= number_with_delimiter(@item24_dashboard.multiple_types["lines"].to_i) %></td>
    <td>$ <%= number_with_delimiter((@item24_dashboard.multiple_types["request"].to_f / 1000).round(0)) %></td>
  </tr>
  <tr><td style="border: 0px"><br></td></tr>
  <thead><tr>
    <th style="border-top: 0px">Funding Request Connection Speed</th>
    <th style="border-top: 0px">Lines</th>
    <th style="border-top: 0px">Requests</th>
  </tr></thead>
<% @item24_dashboard.requests_by_speed.each do |tier| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= @item24_dashboard.speed_tier_names[tier["speed_tier"]] %></td>
    <td><%= number_with_delimiter(tier["lines"].to_i) %></td>
    <td>$ <%= number_with_delimiter(((tier["request"]).to_f / 1000).round(0)) %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>  
  <tr>
    <td><i>Multiple Connection Speeds</i></td>
    <td><%= number_with_delimiter(@item24_dashboard.multiple_speeds["lines"].to_i) %></td>
    <td>$ <%= number_with_delimiter((@item24_dashboard.multiple_speeds["request"].to_f / 1000).round(0)) %></td>
  </tr>

</table>

<p><small><em>All dollar amounts in thousands.</em></small></p>